.SH NAME
.PP
macos-tag \[en] macOS file tags
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]macos-tag\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]command\f[R]]
[[\f[I]tag\f[R] \&...] [\f[I]filename\f[R]]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
List and edit macOS \f[B]Finder\f[R] file tags embedded in the
\f[C]com.apple.metadata:_kMDItemUserTags\f[R] extended file attribute.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \f[C]-h\f[R], \f[C]--help\f[R]
Print help.
.TP
.B \f[C]-v\f[R], \f[C]--version\f[R]
Print version number.
.TP
.B \f[I]tag\f[R]
A case-sensitive tag name.
.TP
.B \f[I]filename\f[R]
Path to a target file.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B \f[C]add\f[R] \f[C]<\f[R]\f[I]tag\f[R] \&...\f[C]>\f[R] \f[C]<\f[R]\f[I]filename\f[R]\f[C]>\f[R]
Add tags to a file.
.TP
.B \f[C]list\f[R] \f[C]<\f[R]\f[I]filename\f[R] \&...\f[C]>\f[R]
List file\[cq]s tags.
.TP
.B \f[C]remove\f[R] \f[C]<\f[R]\f[I]tag\f[R] \&...\f[C]>\f[R] \f[C]<\f[R]\f[I]filename\f[R]\f[C]>\f[R]
Remove tags from a file.
.TP
.B \f[C]reverse\f[R] \f[C]<\f[R]\f[I]filename\f[R]\f[C]>\f[R]
Reverse the order of tags.
.TP
.B \f[C]sort\f[R] \f[C]<\f[R]\f[I]filename\f[R]\f[C]>\f[R]
Sort file\[cq]s tags to alphabetical order.
.SH FILES
.PP
Depends on external programs \f[C]bash\f[R], \f[C]cat\f[R],
\f[C]jq\f[R], \f[C]plutil\f[R], \f[C]xattr\f[R] and \f[C]xxd\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Add tags \f[C]nature\f[R] \f[C]woods\f[R] and \f[C]forest\f[R] to a file
\f[C]picture.jpg\f[R]:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
$ macos-tag add nature woods forest picture.jpg
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
List tags for a \f[C]picture.jpg\f[R]:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
$ macos-tag list picture.jpg
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Remove \f[C]nature\f[R] tag from \f[C]picture.jpg\f[R]:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
$ macos-tag remove nature picture.jpg
\f[R]
.fi
